-- Michael McGlone, Commodity Director, Left S&P Dow Jones Indices
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2013-02-14T17:23:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-14/michael-mcglone-commodity-director-left-s-p-dow-jones-indices.html
Michael McGlone , senior director of
commodity indices at S&P Dow Jones Indices, a joint venture of
CME Group Inc. and The McGraw-Hill Cos., left the company.  McGlone was let go yesterday, he said by phone today.  David Guarino , a spokesman for S&P Dow Jones Indices in New York,
confirmed that McGlone has left the company.  McGlone, 48, worked at S&P for five years, helping to
manage and develop new indices at one point and another
calculating the annual rebalancing. S&P Indices merged with Dow
Jones Indexes in July last year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  